# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Go HTTP server + DynamoDB with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
go mod tidy
```

### 3. Run the server

```bash
go run .
```

Server starts on http://localhost:3000.

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /items | Create an item |
| GET | /items | List all items |
| GET | /items/{id} | Get an item |
| DELETE | /items/{id} | Delete an item |

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/items \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"id":"1","name":"Widget"}'

curl http://localhost:3000/items/1
```

## Testing

```bash
go test ./...
```

Tests use `sdk.New()` for in-process CloudMock — zero network overhead, ~20μs per operation.

## CloudMock DevTools

Open [http://localhost:4500](http://localhost:4500) to explore traces and topology.
